President Biden has announced his intention to nominate former Maryland Governor Martin O'Malley as Commissioner of the Social Security Administration. O'Malley is described as a lifelong public servant who has focused on making government more accessible and transparent. As Mayor of Baltimore and Governor of Maryland, he utilized data and performance-driven technologies to address community challenges. President Biden believes that O'Malley will be a strong partner in protecting Social Security for future generations. O'Malley has a background in using performance management and customer service technologies in government and has written extensively on governing for better results in the Information Age. He holds a B.A. from Catholic University and a J.D. from the University of Maryland School of Law.